SIMPLE: polytype
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polytype
<hw>Pol"y*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> +
<ets>-type</ets>: cf. F. <ets>polytype</ets>, a.]</ety>
<fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>A cast, or facsimile copy, of an engraved
block, matter in type, etc.; <as>as, a <ex>polytype</ex> in
relief</as></def> -- <wordforms><wf>Pol"y*type</wf>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><q>By pressing the wood cut into semifluid metal, an intaglio matrix
is produced: and from this matrix, in a similar way, a
<qex>polytype</qex> in relief is obtained.</q>
<rj><qau>Hansard.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polytype</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Polytype
<hw>Pol"y*type</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>Of or
pertaining to polytypes; obtained by polytyping; <as>as, a
<ex>polytype</ex> plate</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polytype</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Polytype
<hw>Pol"y*type</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Polytyped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Polytyping</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <fld>(Print.)</fld>
<def>To produce a polytype of; <as>as, to <ex>polytype</ex> an
engraving</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polyurethane</ent>⟦br⟧
